NKD-6108 Fixes Apple Sign In being unable to use separate credentials per store view.

Five root causes combined to make per-store Apple configuration impossible:

1. Key.php compared $this->getScope() (plural: "stores"/"websites") against singular
   ScopeInterface constants, so the ternary for $scopeCode always resolved to null,
   causing SQLSTATE[23000] Column 'scope_id' cannot be null on strict MySQL.
   Fix: use $this->getScopeId() which is always correctly set by Magento.

2. Token/Apple::generateSecret() always wrote the generated secret to SCOPE_TYPE_DEFAULT/0
   regardless of which store view was being configured. Fix: accept $scope/$scopeId params
   and write to the correct scope.

3. Token/Apple::generateSecret() read all Apple credentials (key_file_content, key_id,
   team_id, application_id) without passing any scope, always resolving from the default
   store context in admin. Since the JWT secret encodes application_id in its sub claim,
   secrets generated for one store's credentials are invalid for another store's Apple app.
   Fix: thread scope params through all internal getNetworkConfig() calls.

4. Key.php called generateSecret() after writing key_file_content to the database, but
   Magento's in-memory config cache still held the old (empty) value, so getKey() returned
   false and secret generation was silently skipped on first save. Fix: pass the raw key
   content directly to generateSecret() as $rawKey to bypass the stale cache read.

5. RegenerateButton.php built the regenerate URL without store/website params, so the
   controller always processed the request as default scope and reported a missing key
   error for non-default store views. Fix: forward the current store/website request param.

Additionally fixed RegenerateAppleSecretKey controller which used singular scope type
constants ("store"/"website") instead of plural writer-format ("stores"/"websites"),
had if/if instead of if/elseif (allowing both store and website to overwrite each other),
and had scopeCode/scopeType params swapped in the getNetworkConfig() key existence check.

